	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-15328">
		<article id="comment-15328" class="comment-inner">

            <div class="flex-row align-top">
                <div class="flex-col">
                    <div class="comment-author mr-half">
                        <img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/27110c3504ba550a5d5ac0a2d87d03e9?s=70&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/27110c3504ba550a5d5ac0a2d87d03e9?s=140&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-70 photo' height='70' width='70' />                    </div>
                </div><!-- .large-3 -->

                <div class="flex-col flex-grow">
                    <cite class="strong fn">Beverly</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>                    
                   <div class="comment-content"><p>I am 52 and have been unsuccessful with controlling armpit odor for as long as I can remember.  When I got married and realized that my husband could go several days without the need to shower or reapply deodorant I knew that I wanted to find that kind of power for my armpits.  This may not happen to everyone who struggles with finding the right deodorant but in my case it ruled my life.  I had to consider my armpit odor for every social event, my odor was robbing my self confidence.  I have tried every deodorant on the market for both men and women, I have shopped the European markets for my answer, nothing worked.  I have an 18 year old son and a 20 year old daughter.  My daughter has the armpits of a goddess, but unfortunately my son shares my burden.  The last couple of years I have been reading and experimenting with products that claim to kill bacteria.  I have officially and completely burnt out my armpits twice, full scab, the whole pit.  But I must press on because I have managed to pass this problem on to my son.  Through trial and error and the process of elimination I have come across a series of products that control my odor very well, but I must apply 7 different topicals and wait for each layer to dry before applying the next.  I have had great success with my home made concoction but for my son it was hit and miss.  I was on the internet on night and came across the deodorant &#8220;My Goodness&#8221;.  It was new to me so it got my attention.  As I always do I read the ingredients to see if anything in this deodorant would be one of my known offenders.  Instead I found the opposite.  Almost every ingredient in the deodorant is in my home made concoction plus a few more.  The extra ingredients are also ones I have read up on but had not incorporated into my routine.  The deodorant was pricey but I had to try it.  Because I have already been using magnesium oil for a couple of years I started out with Max formulation.  The day after I received it my son and I both tried it.  Both of us had great success.  Before finding &#8220;My Goodness&#8221; my son could get in the car with me and my daughter and it would be so hard to think of anything except his odor, this could be even right after showering.  I felt so bad for my son because I already know how hard it is to go through life wondering if people were talking about me or being excluded from social events because other people don&#8217;t want to be around you.  On the first use we both had success.  My son smelled so good that I could cry.  Several days have past, no more hit or miss.  He smells great repeatedly.  He always tried to make me believe that his odor  problem didn&#8217;t bother him that much, that it wasn&#8217;t that big of a deal, but I can tell you from the first time that I told him that he smelled great that a burden had been lifted off of him.  I will continue to use this product.  I am looking forward to trying some of their other formulations and scents.</p>
</div>


